Read AGENTS.md first. Full playbook: docs/CURSOR_CODEX_COLLABORATION.md.

## Core

- **Cursor** is the in-repo orchestrator (plan, review, PR, merge path).
- **Codex** (IDE panel or `agent-codex-*` cloud) is a code specialist — not architecture or release authority.
- **ChatGPT Desktop** remains stack-level planner for briefs/classification; do not conflict with AGENTS.md hierarchy.

## Per task

1. Classify: architecture / code / debug / refactor / UI / docs / mixed.
2. Pick mode: Cursor-led | Codex-assisted | Codex-led | **Collaborative** (default for serious work).
3. Branch: `agent-cursor-*` or `agent-codex-*` — one writer per branch; never `main`.
4. Codex only on scoped briefs; no Cursor-owned paths (`middleware.ts`, `app/api/*`, `lib/env.ts`, `lib/didit.ts`) without Cursor review.

## Prohibited

Blind delegation; Codex on trivial edits; Codex architecture alone; unrelated file churn; auto-deploy; secret/env changes; skip verification; push to `main`.

## End of task — report

- Working mode used
- Files changed · what was implemented · why Codex was/wasn't used
- Verification performed · remaining risks · recommended next step
